BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: College Park Cavalier Band Booster Club

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: To provide necessary support for all band activites at The Woodlands College Park High School in the Conore Independent School District. There are approximately 295 students in The Woodlands College Park High School Band
IRS990.MissionDesc: The Woodlands College Park Cavalier Band Booster Club provides support to the student band activities throughout the year.
IRS990.Desc: The Woodlands College Park Cavalier Band Booster Club provides for competition fees and travel for band students.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: The Booster Club provides music expenses including copyright fees, drill writing and marching show music, and instruction to band students.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: The Booster Club provides band equipment, maintenance and repairs, and marching band show props and uniforms.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Program Service Expenses 40,958, Grants and allocations 0, Revenue 32,100 The booster club provides general support to band students

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Form 990 tax return is presented to the board for approval prior to submission to the Internal Revenue Service
